# 5. 選んだ道

Emu: ...
Plushies: ...
Plushies: Hey, did something happen with Emu?
Plushies: Yeah, she's been sitting on that bench and staring off into space for a really long time now.
Plushies: I'm a little worried. Should we try and go talk to her...? Huh?
KAITO: Emu, there you are.
Emu: KAITO... What are you doing here?
KAITO: I've been looking for you.
KAITO: I kept wondering how you were doing after we spoke last, so I've been taking peeks here and there using your phone...
Emu: Oh...
KAITO: Mind if I sit next to you?
Emu: Sure, sit here!
KAITO: I'm sorry for eavesdropping on your conversation with Byakkomachi.
Emu: No, that's okay. I really appreciate you worrying about me.
KAITO: Are you feeling okay...?
Emu: ...
Emu: Suzu told me that she's really scared...
Emu: And I think I kinda understand what she's going through right now. Because I felt the same thing when we were trying to save Phoenix Wonderland...
KAITO: ...
Emu: They started tearing down the old rides and replacing them with new ones...
Emu: And I remember the look on the guests' faces as they watched their favorite rides slowly disappear.
Emu: I became so scared of disappointing all the people who'd been coming to the park for a really long time...
KAITO: Of course...
KAITO: Change things or keep them the same. Both end up being scary choices...
Emu: *Nod*
KAITO: What if you tried talking to someone who went through the same experience, Emu...?
Emu: Someone who went through the same experience?
KAITO: Yes. When Phoenix Wonderland was in trouble...
KAITO: Who were the first people that tried to turn things around for the park?
Emu: Are you talking about...?
KAITO: Those people...
KAITO: They must've had to overcome the same sort of fear Byakkomachi is feeling right now, yes?
Emu: Oh...
Keisuke: You wish to know what we were thinking as we tried to reestablish Phoenix Wonderland as a viable enterprise?
Emu: Yeah...! I wanna know what you guys felt back then!
Emu: Weren't you afraid of all the changes that were coming?
Emu: Wasn't the thought of disappointing everyone really scary? Were you ever worried that you were taking the park down the wrong path...?
Shosuke: What? Why are you asking us these questions now?
Shosuke: Well, truth be told... Many of those around us were opposed to our choices.
Shosuke: I'd be lying if I said that we never worried or felt scared.
Emu: Really...?
Keisuke: Yes, really. Some even said that we should scrap the park altogether in order to build something else.
Keisuke: By that point, Phoenix Wonderland had an established history.
Keisuke: Its reputation was effectively set in stone, which made attracting new demographics a nearly impossible task.
Shosuke: In other words, starting over from scratch would've been easier.
Emu: ...
Keisuke: But we didn't want to do that. Even if it meant that the park would change drastically, we didn't want Phoenix Wonderland to disappear.
Keisuke: And we came up with the best ideas we could to prevent it.
Emu: You guys were scared... How did you overcome that and move forward?
Shosuke: It didn't matter that we were worried or feeling scared. We had to move forward.
Shosuke: Because reality wasn't going to wait for us to get all our ducks in a row.
Keisuke: Right. We definitely didn't have the luxury of time.
Keisuke: We had to come up with as many ideas as we could in a short period and choose the best ones...
Keisuke: Nobody knew what the right answer was. But...
Keisuke: Our task became to turn our choice into the correct solution.
Emu: Turn your choice into the correct solution...?
Shosuke: That being said...
Shosuke: You and your friends came along partway through, and sent us on a completely different course.
Keisuke: True. However, if we had ended up partnering with Riley Entertainment...
Keisuke: We would've stuck with that decision.
Emu: Oh...
Keisuke: Once you've made up your mind, it becomes easier to make scary decisions.
Keisuke: So, the problem becomes a matter of resolve.
Emu: I see...
Shosuke: I don't know what's on your mind right now...
Shosuke: But I'll leave you with this.
Shosuke: I'm sure you'll do just fine, Emu.
Emu: Huh?
Keisuke: Yes, I agree.
Keisuke: You and your friends are the reason Phoenix Wonderland is thriving right now.
Keisuke: So, I'm sure you'll find a solution that will make everyone happy.
Emu: ...!
Emu: Keisuke, Shosuke...
Emu: Thanks, you guys!
Emu: What do you think?
Byakkomachi: Interesting...
Byakkomachi: This idea could help us deal with all three problems at once. Ticket prices, member retention and the quality of their performances.
Emu: Really?!
Byakkomachi: Yes. It's a bold idea, but we should be able to turn it into a presentable proposal after we hammer out all the details.
Emu: Woohoo!!
Byakkomachi: However...
Byakkomachi: There's no telling how Morinomiya's fans are going to react. This may result in even greater backlash...
Emu: Oh...
Emu: I know how you feel, Suzu.
Emu: You're scared that you're going to disappoint even more fans.
Emu: But...
Emu: If you just keep things as is... If you don't do something, then the thing you really care about is going to vanish someday.
Emu: Which is why I think everyone is trying to get past the fear and move forward...
Emu: Nobody knows what the right answer is...
Emu: You just have to turn your choice into the correct solution...
Byakkomachi: ...
Byakkomachi: Turning my choice into the correct solution... I like that.
Emu: Me too! My brothers said that to me.
Byakkomachi: Thank you, Otori.
Byakkomachi: Would you mind bearing with me for just a bit longer?
Emu: Huh?
Byakkomachi: Before any ideas are presented to the board, they first need to be approved by the chairman.
Byakkomachi: So, in order to convince my grandfather, I'd like to hash out the details with you.
Emu: Yeah, of course!
